Vice President Biden met with Croatian Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor to discuss Croatia's European Union candidacy. The Vice President expressed strong support for Croatia and commended their cooperation with the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia. He also acknowledged Croatia's economic reforms, commitment to combat corruption, and contributions to NATO operations, particularly in Afghanistan. The Vice President praised Croatia's efforts to foster stability and good relations in Southeast Europe, including reaching a solution on a long-standing border dispute with Slovenia. He also commended Croatia's efforts to develop a closer relationship with Serbia, support Kosovo, and assist in reforming the Bosnian state.